<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head') %>
</head>
<body>

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<main>

  <!-- ── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="hero" style="padding: 3rem 0;">
    <div class="hero__image-slot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero__content">
        <span class="hero__eyebrow">Who We Are</span>
        <h1>About the Alliance</h1>
        <p class="hero__description">
          The McNutt's Island Alliance is a community organization dedicated to
          the stewardship, celebration, and future of McNutt's Island, Nova Scotia.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Mission ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Our Mission</span>
      <h2>What We're Here to Do</h2>
      <p>
        The McNutt's Island Alliance exists to connect the people who care about this island —
        residents and property owners, researchers and historians, the fishing community,
        visitors, and those who simply love this place from a distance — and to give that
        care a form.
      </p>
      <p>
        We are not a government agency, a conservation land trust, or a developer. We are
        neighbours and advocates: people who believe that a place this historically significant
        and ecologically valuable deserves a community paying attention to it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our work falls into three broad areas:
      </p>
      <ul style="line-height: 2.2; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        <li><strong>Documentation</strong> — building the record of the island's history, ecology, and community</li>
        <li><strong>Stewardship</strong> — supporting the lighthouse preservation society, monitoring environmental health, promoting responsible access</li>
        <li><strong>Conversation</strong> — creating space for the difficult and important questions about the island's future, including the naming question</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Who We Are ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">The Community</span>
      <h2>Who Belongs to the Alliance</h2>
      <p>
        Alliance membership is open to anyone with a connection to McNutt's Island —
        and we interpret "connection" broadly. Current and former island residents.
        Property owners. People whose families have fished the harbour for generations.
        Researchers. Lighthouse enthusiasts. South Shore Nova Scotians with roots in
        the community. Birders who've made the crossing once and never forgotten it.
      </p>
      <p>
        There are no fees. No obligations beyond adding your name. The directory is simply
        a record that this community exists — and a starting point for the conversations
        and relationships that follow.
      </p>
      <a href="/community" class="btn btn--primary mt-3">Join the Alliance</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Acknowledgment ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Land Acknowledgment</span>
      <h2>Mi'kma'ki</h2>
      <p>
        McNutt's Island and the surrounding waters lie within Mi'kma'ki, the ancestral
        and unceded territory of the Mi'kmaq people. The Mi'kmaq have lived in relationship
        with this land and these waters for at least ten thousand years.
      </p>
      <p>
        We acknowledge this history and our responsibility as guests on this land.
        We are committed to engaging in genuine partnership with Mi'kmaq communities —
        including the Sipekne'katik First Nation — as we navigate questions of the island's
        future and, specifically, the question of its name.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Contact ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Get in Touch</span>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about the Alliance, the island, or this website, please reach out
        through our community directory or via email. We are a volunteer organization
        and respond to messages as quickly as we can.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@mcnuttsisland.org">hello@mcnuttsisland.org</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        For media inquiries, research partnerships, or questions about the naming conversation,
        please contact us by email with a brief description of your interest.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        <a href="/community" class="btn btn--outline-dark">Join the Alliance</a>
        &nbsp;
        <a href="/bearing-witness" class="btn btn--outline-dark">Share Your Story</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
<script src="/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
